Courtesy of #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - The Democratic Alliance wants Parliament to investigate the Phala Phala farm robbery scandal. It's written to the National Assembly Speaker Nosiviwe Mapisa-Nqakula, asking her to establish an urgent ad hoc committee. READ: Ramaphosa farm theft | Let the law run its course, says Mbeki However, the party says it will not be deterred by the president dodging questions. "We’ll continue to ask questions, we'll continue to push for answers," said DA Chief Whip Natasha Mazzone.